            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "An obfuchsia can alter the color and texture of its foliage to blend in with its environment. Whenever an obfuchsia remains motionless for 1 round, it gains a +10 bonus to Stealth checks (this bonus doesn\u2019t stack with <i>invisibility</i> or similar effects). If the obfuchsia moves more than 10 feet or takes a hostile action (such as attacking), it loses this bonus until it once again spends 1 round remaining still.",
                "name": "Camouflage",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "An obfuchsia vibrates thin membranes between its tendrils to cancel sound waves in an atmosphere, generating an aura of silence that lasts until the beginning of the obfuchsia\u2019s next turn. Creatures within 10 feet, including the obfuchsia, are deafened (Fort DC 19). Sound-based sense-dependent effects, including blindsight (sound), cannot pass through the emanation. This aura of silence is not strong enough to stop sonic weapons, however, which function normally. If the obfuchsia can't take actions, its aura is suppressed.",
                "name": "Silence",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            }
